Program: Outlook
Title: Outlook Weekend: The Blink
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cswt5x
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 17 Jun 2018
When Rikke Schmit Kjaegaard fell seriously ill with bacterial meningitis no one thought she would make it. She survived but found herself in a terrifying situation, she couldn't talk and the only part of her body she could move was her eyes. At first, no one was aware she was conscious, but her husband noticed her attempts to communicate through the blink of her eyes. Image: Close up image of an eye Credit: cosmin4000/iStock/Getty Images Plus Presenter: Saskia Edwards Show less